<item>
            <title>[SOLR-7369] AngularJS UI insufficient URLDecoding in cloud/tree view</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7369</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The new Angular Admin UI has problems showing nodes in the &lt;tt&gt;cloud-&amp;gt;tree&lt;/tt&gt; men on level 2 or containing &lt;tt&gt;/&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;_&lt;/tt&gt;. You get ugly exception instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reason is that these come escaped in link and the &lt;tt&gt;cloud.js&lt;/tt&gt; script only attempts to replace first &lt;tt&gt;%2F=&amp;gt;/&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12819630">SOLR-7369</key>
            <summary>AngularJS UI insufficient URLDecoding in cloud/tree view</summary>
